description: "Naming"
globs:
  - "**/*.go"
alwaysApply: true
---
- Use short names for local variables, long names for exported functions.
- Name interfaces with the `-er` suffix when appropriate: `Reader`, `Writer`, `Handler`.
- Use `camelCase` for unexported names, `PascalCase` for exported names.
- Name constants in `PascalCase` depending on context.
- Use single-letter names only for indices: `i`, `j`, `k`, for reader - `r`, for writer - `w`.
- Avoid abbreviations unless they are commonly accepted (HTTP, URL, ID, DB).
- Name boolean variables as questions: `isValid`, `hasError`, `canProcess`.
- Use verbs for functions: `GetUser`, `CreateOrder`, `ValidateInput`.
- Use nouns for types: `User`, `Order`, `Config`.
- Name tests as `TestFunctionName_Scenario`: `TestProcessTransaction_InvalidAmount`.
